thread.title: Royals' Mike Moustakas hits questionable home run in Game 6

author: USA TODAY Sports
title: Royals' Mike Moustakas hits questionable home run in Game 6
text:
Mike Moustakas reacts after hitting a solo home run in the second inning. (Photo: Peter Aiken, USA TODAY Sports)
34 CONNECT 46 TWEET LINKEDIN 6 COMMENT EMAIL MORE Kansas City Royals third baseman Mike Moustakas hit a home run in Game 6 of the American League Championship Series against the Toronto Blue Jays that will be remembered for a long time.
The homer by Moustakas, his first of this postseason, was caught by a Royals fan at the top of the right-field wall at Kauffman Stadium, bringing back memories of then 12-year old fan Jeffrey Maier, who interfered with a Derek Jeter home run ball in Game 1 of the 1996 ALCS between the New York Yankees and Baltimore Orioles.
Blue Jays right fielder Jose Bautista immediately signaled for interference. The umpires reviewed the play but determined there was not enough evidence to rule fan interference.and upheld, giving the Royals an early 2-0 lead.
FOR THE WIN
Royals benefit from questionable home-run call in Game 6
Royals fan, Caleb Humphreys, a 19-year-old fan from Blue Springs, Missouri, became an instant celebrity. Humphreys kept the ball and was hounded by reporters, including Fox's Erin Andrews on the national broadcast.
I think this is definitive proof that the fan reached over @MLB #NotAHomeRun #ComeTogether pic.twitter.com/IEEjeK3d4l
